# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AI Proxy — Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# You need at least ONE provider configured to start the proxy.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Anthropic (Claude models) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at https://platform.claude.com
# IMPORTANT: Add credits at https://platform.claude.com under Billing.
# Without credits you will get a "Your credit balance is too low" error.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── OpenAI (GPT models) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at https://platform.openai.com
# When set, gpt-* model requests route directly to OpenAI.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Google Gemini ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at https://aistudio.google.com
# When set, gemini-* model requests route to Google Gemini.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Ollama (free local models — no API key needed) ────────────────────────────
# Install Ollama from https://ollama.com — completely free, runs on your machine.
# Set OLLAMA_BASE_URL to enable it, then list which models you have pulled.
#
# To pull a model:   ollama pull llama3
# Available models:  llama3, mistral, codellama, phi3, qwen2, deepseek-r1, gemma3
#
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODELS=llama3,mistral,codellama

# ── Fallback (auto-retry on failure) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# If the primary provider returns an error (429, 500, 502, 503, 529),
# the proxy automatically retries the next available provider in this list.
#
# Example: if Anthropic hits a rate limit, it falls back to OpenAI automatically.
# The order here sets the priority — first entry is tried first.
#
# Only enabled providers (with keys set above) are used.
# FALLBACK_ORDER=anthropic,openai,gemini,ollama

# ── PROXY_API_KEY — Password protection ───────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does:
#   Adds a password layer so only people who know this key can use your proxy.
#   Anyone connecting must send this value as their API key in their tool.
#
# When to use it:
#   - Running on a server (deployed online)  → ALWAYS set this
#   - Sharing with teammates over a network  → ALWAYS set this
#   - Running locally for yourself only      → Safe to leave blank
#
# PROXY_API_KEY=

# ── CORS_ORIGIN — Browser access control ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# Controls which websites running in a browser can call your proxy.
#   * (default)                  → Allow any website (fine for local use)
#   https://myapp.com            → Only allow your specific app
#   http://localhost:5173        → Only allow a local frontend (e.g. Vite)
#
# Note: CLI tools (Claude Code, curl) are NOT affected by CORS.
# CORS_ORIGIN=*

# ── Other settings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Port (default 3030)
# PORT=3030

# Request timeout in milliseconds (default 120000 = 2 minutes)
# Increase for slow models or very long documents.
# REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS=120000

# Rate limit per IP per minute (default 60, set to 0 to disable)
# Protects against abuse if PROXY_API_KEY is shared on a server.
# RATE_LIMIT_PER_MIN=60
